📅 Day 3 — Lazy Evaluation & Transformations
📌 Concepts Covered
🔹 Lazy Evaluation

Spark does not execute transformations immediately.

Instead:

Transformations are recorded

Execution happens only when an action is triggered

This allows Spark to optimize the execution plan before running the job.

🔹 Transformations

Transformations create a new RDD or DataFrame from an existing one.

Two main types:

Narrow Transformations

Data remains within the same partition

No data shuffling required

Examples:

map()

filter()

Wide Transformations

Data moves across partitions

Requires data shuffling

Examples:

groupBy

reduceByKey

🔹 Transformations vs Actions
Type	Description
Transformations	Define operations on data
Actions	Trigger execution and return results

Spark executes the RDD lineage only when an action is called.

