📅 Day 4 — Spark Execution Architecture
📌 Concepts Covered
🔹 Job

A job is triggered whenever an action is executed in Spark.

🔹 Stage

A job is divided into multiple stages based on shuffle boundaries.

🔹 Task

Smallest unit of execution

Runs on a single partition

🔹 DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph)

Spark builds a DAG of transformations before executing a job.

This helps Spark to:

Optimize execution

Reduce unnecessary computations

